1. Definitions

   1.1 "Commercial License" means a written agreement between You and the
       Licensor that authorizes use of the Software beyond the scope of this
       WPEL.

   1.2 "Commercial Purpose" means any use, direct or indirect, that is
       primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage,
       monetary compensation, or revenue generation, including without
       limitation: offering the Software or any derivative work as a hosted
       or managed service; incorporating the Software into a product or
       service offered to third parties for a fee or other consideration;
       using the Software to provide paid consulting, support, or
       professional services; or use in connection with Internal Business
       Operations.

   1.3 "Derivative Work" means any work based upon or derived from the
       Software, including modifications, adaptations, translations, or
       other changes, whether or not recognizable as such.

   1.4 "Educational Institution" means an accredited school, college,
       university, or other recognized non-profit educational body whose
       primary purpose is teaching, academic research, or scholarship.

   1.5 "Educational Use" means use of the Software by an individual student,
       instructor, or academic researcher solely for:

       (a) personal learning or self-study;
       (b) classroom instruction, coursework, teaching, or academic
           demonstrations;
       (c) non-commercial academic research, thesis work, or publication of
           research results, provided such research is not funded primarily
           for the commercial benefit of a third party; or
       (d) participation in a non-commercial student project, hackathon, or
           competition.

       Educational Use does not include use by an Educational Institution
       (or any department, lab, or IT unit thereof) for Internal Business
       Operations, administrative systems, institutional infrastructure,
       Production Use, or any Commercial Purpose — even if the institution is
       non-profit.

   1.6 "Internal Business Operations" means the day-to-day operations,
       administration, management, or production activities of an
       Organization, including IT operations, employee tooling, customer
       support systems, back-office workflows, and any use that supports the
       Organization's mission beyond pure classroom instruction or individual
       academic research as defined in Educational Use.

   1.7 "Licensor" means Improba, the copyright holder of the Software, and
       its successors and assigns.

   1.8 "Organization" means any legal entity or identifiable group, including
       without limitation: corporations, partnerships, sole proprietorships,
       limited liability companies, government agencies, non-profit entities,
       foundations, associations, cooperatives, and Educational Institutions
       acting in their institutional capacity.

   1.9 "Personal Use" means use of the Software by a natural person acting
       in their individual capacity for private, non-professional purposes,
       where the use is not performed on behalf of, at the direction of, or
       for the benefit of any Organization, and is not for any Commercial
       Purpose.

   1.10 "Production Use" means use of the Software to process real data,
        support live users, run business-critical workflows, or otherwise
        operate in an environment intended for ongoing operational reliance,
        as distinct from evaluation, prototyping, classroom demonstration,
        or personal experimentation.

   1.11 "Software" means the Workproba software made available by the
        Licensor under this WPEL, including source code, object code,
        binaries, documentation, and associated materials, and any official
        updates or releases thereof provided by the Licensor.

   1.12 "You" (or "Your") means the individual or legal entity exercising
        permissions granted by this WPEL.

