4. Commercial License Required

   4.1 The grant in Section 3 does not apply, and You must obtain a
       Commercial License, if the Software is used or accessed:

       (a) by or on behalf of any Organization for any purpose;
       (b) for Internal Business Operations of any kind;
       (c) for Production Use;
       (d) for any Commercial Purpose; or
       (e) in any manner not expressly permitted as Personal Use or
           Educational Use.

   4.2 Without limiting Section 4.1, the following require a Commercial
       License:

       (a) deployment within a company, government body, hospital, NGO, or
           Educational Institution for staff, students (beyond individual
           Educational Use), or institutional systems;
       (b) use by contractors, consultants, or employees in connection with
           professional duties;
       (c) offering the Software (or any service built upon it) to third
           parties, whether or not for a fee;
       (d) use in connection with funded research where the funder receives
           commercial rights or the primary beneficiary is a commercial
           entity; and
       (e) bundling, sublicensing, or redistributing the Software as part of
           a commercial product or service.

   4.3 Evaluation. An Organization may download and evaluate the Software
       internally for up to thirty (30) days without a Commercial License,
       solely to determine whether to enter into one. Any use beyond
       evaluation, or any Production Use during evaluation, requires a
       Commercial License.

